WEBVTT

00:01.088 --> 00:03.046
- Previously, on "You"...

00:03.090 --> 00:06.267
- Everyone just calls me Beck.
And you're Joe...

00:06.310 --> 00:07.790
- Goldberg.

00:07.833 --> 00:09.835
People find the one.
I believe that.

00:09.879 --> 00:13.230
I was in love, once.
Candace, she broke my heart.

00:13.274 --> 00:15.145
Beck, I should have
seen the signs.

00:15.189 --> 00:16.755
But we never do.

00:16.799 --> 00:19.106
Exhibit A.
Claudia, single parent.

00:19.149 --> 00:22.544
You think she knew Ron was a
shitbag when she fell in love?

00:22.587 --> 00:23.980
- You're a freak,
so stay away from Paco.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.590
Because if you don't,
I'm going to grab

00:25.634 --> 00:27.505
a steak knife, and I'll
cut those freak eyes out.

00:27.549 --> 00:29.420
- A guy needs to
protect himself.

00:29.464 --> 00:32.075
I had to be sure you are safe.

00:32.119 --> 00:34.860
I just need to know
who you really are.

00:34.904 --> 00:38.081
You're smart.
- Shit, my phone.

00:38.125 --> 00:39.865
Must have
dropped it in the subway.

00:39.909 --> 00:42.433
- Except in the ways
you are really not,

00:42.477 --> 00:44.087
like not locking your phone.

00:44.131 --> 00:46.872
And that means
I'm still logged into you.

00:46.916 --> 00:48.091
Maybe we could
get a drink sometime?

00:48.135 --> 00:49.484
- Sure.

00:49.527 --> 00:51.312
- Hell, maybe I'm just
a fool in love.

00:51.355 --> 00:53.140
It just feels right.

00:53.183 --> 00:55.446
I'm going to help you
get the life you deserve.

00:55.490 --> 00:58.232
You have
questionable taste in friends.

00:58.275 --> 01:01.452
- Hey, man,
I'm thinking, maybe--

01:01.496 --> 01:03.454
- You fall for the wrong men.

01:03.498 --> 01:05.500
Get up on the fence!

01:08.155 --> 01:10.940
Beck, were you ever
sleeping with your therapist?

01:10.983 --> 01:14.944
- Yes, I cheated,
but it's over now.

01:14.987 --> 01:16.250
- What he did to me,
one of these days,

01:16.293 --> 01:17.773
he's going to do to you.

01:17.816 --> 01:21.037
Maybe he'll do whatever
the hell he did to Candace.

01:21.081 --> 01:22.299
- I need you to tell me
what happened with Candace.

01:22.343 --> 01:24.214
- Why, why does
that even matter?

01:24.258 --> 01:27.130
- Because there's no evidence
that she was in Italy at all.

01:27.174 --> 01:30.046
No one's heard a single word
from her since she left.

01:30.090 --> 01:32.570
- I know you, you won't
stop asking questions

01:32.614 --> 01:34.355
until I do
something about this.

01:34.398 --> 01:38.098
- [whispering]
What the hell?

01:38.141 --> 01:39.490
[gasps]

01:39.534 --> 01:41.101
I'll call you later.

01:41.144 --> 01:44.191
- This, Beck,
is between me and you.

01:44.234 --> 01:47.194
[dramatic music]

01:47.237 --> 01:51.285
♪

01:51.328 --> 01:54.679
- Joe, Joe!

01:58.205 --> 02:01.164
[soft music]

02:01.208 --> 02:08.215
♪

02:17.876 --> 02:19.356
- Please, I'm sorry.
- Move, move!

02:19.400 --> 02:20.923
- I was just
organizing the shelves.

02:20.966 --> 02:23.143
- You think you know
my business better than I do?

02:23.186 --> 02:26.624
Get in, and you'll stay in
until you understand!

02:26.668 --> 02:27.669
- Understand what?

02:27.712 --> 02:30.106
- Who I am to you.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.108
[dramatic music]

02:32.152 --> 02:33.544
♪

02:33.588 --> 02:35.894
[pounding]

02:35.938 --> 02:37.548
- Joe!

02:49.995 --> 02:51.475
Joe!

02:53.825 --> 02:55.218
Joe!

02:55.262 --> 02:58.221
[ominous music]

02:58.265 --> 03:02.443
♪

03:02.486 --> 03:04.445
- I'm here.

03:09.101 --> 03:10.451
- [softly]
Joe.

03:15.456 --> 03:18.633
Why...

03:18.676 --> 03:20.548
am I in here?

03:22.332 --> 03:25.292
- Well, that's good,
because we're talking.

03:25.335 --> 03:26.510
We're getting it
out in the open.

03:26.554 --> 03:30.210
- You hit me!
- I'm sorry.

03:30.253 --> 03:31.689
Beck, I'm sorry.

03:31.733 --> 03:33.648
I just--I didn't
want you to freak out.

03:33.691 --> 03:38.261
- Joe, I am locked
in a glass cage!

03:38.305 --> 03:40.045
- Temporarily.

03:42.570 --> 03:44.833
- How long?
- What?

03:44.876 --> 03:48.358
- How long are you going
to keep me in here?

03:48.402 --> 03:50.317
If this is just temporary.

03:50.360 --> 03:52.362
- Oh, honestly, I haven't
thought that far ahead.

03:52.406 --> 03:54.756
I--I--

03:54.799 --> 03:58.890
I just--I need to know
that I can trust you

03:58.934 --> 04:02.894
to see the truth.
- What truth is that?

04:02.938 --> 04:07.508
- Everything I have done,
I have done for you.

04:07.551 --> 04:10.380
- Even this?

04:10.424 --> 04:11.990
- Even this.

04:17.387 --> 04:20.608
Oh, God.
- [crying]

04:20.651 --> 04:24.351
- I wish I knew
what you were thinking.

04:24.394 --> 04:27.397
Tell me.

04:27.441 --> 04:30.400
[tense music]

04:30.444 --> 04:31.532
♪

04:31.575 --> 04:34.186
- What's in the box?

04:34.230 --> 04:37.320
Tell me.

04:37.364 --> 04:39.017
Tell me I'm crazy.

04:39.061 --> 04:44.371
Tell me you didn't
kill Benji.

04:45.633 --> 04:48.897
Tell me you didn't kill Peach.

04:50.681 --> 04:53.684
- If you knew what I knew.
- [sharp exhale]

04:55.251 --> 04:57.862
[sobbing]

04:57.906 --> 05:00.561
- Shit, Beck, that's right.
You have no idea.

05:00.604 --> 05:03.346
I promised you the truth,
and I'm going to give you that.

05:03.390 --> 05:06.480
- [sobs]

05:06.523 --> 05:09.396
Wait, Joe.
Don't leave!

05:09.439 --> 05:11.963
- I'm not.

05:12.007 --> 05:15.184
We're going
to get through this.

05:15.227 --> 05:16.968
- Joe...

05:17.012 --> 05:19.144
[pounds on glass]
Joe!

05:19.188 --> 05:21.233
No, Joe!

05:21.277 --> 05:23.323
Joe, Joe!

05:25.063 --> 05:28.328
[high-pitched ringing]

05:29.677 --> 05:30.939
[soft dramatic music]

05:30.982 --> 05:33.768
- That could have gone worse.

05:33.811 --> 05:37.554
I knew you'd be scared.
That's why I tried

05:37.598 --> 05:39.469
to protect you from the truth.
[phone dings]

05:39.513 --> 05:43.560
And now, I need to
protect us from the world,

05:43.604 --> 05:45.954
long enough to work this out.

05:45.997 --> 05:50.219
So, business as usual.
They're the best cover.

05:50.262 --> 05:52.526
As far as your friends
are concerned,

05:52.569 --> 05:54.484
you're going off the grid.

05:54.528 --> 05:57.400
[keys clacking]

05:57.444 --> 06:00.621
And it wouldn't be
a true social media detox

06:00.664 --> 06:03.363
without announcing it
to the world.

06:08.237 --> 06:10.500
I'll be back soon.
The basement is off limits

06:10.544 --> 06:11.893
until I finish
open heart surgery

06:11.936 --> 06:13.982
on a first edition
Sylvia Plath.

06:14.025 --> 06:17.115
- Nice, uh, what kind
of condition is she in?

06:17.159 --> 06:20.641
- Fragile.
She's very fragile.

06:20.684 --> 06:23.687
- Evidence, evidence
is all I need

06:23.731 --> 06:27.561
to prove to you
I'm not some sicko.

06:27.604 --> 06:30.694
I'm your protector.
You'll see.

06:30.738 --> 06:34.655
[sirens wailing]

06:34.698 --> 06:36.526
- Let's skip the
"nothing to see here."

06:36.570 --> 06:38.485
Get straight to moving along.
- No, this is my building.

06:38.528 --> 06:40.443
That's my neighbor, Claudia.
- Your neighbor, huh?

06:40.487 --> 06:41.836
- Yeah.
- So then you know the piece

06:41.879 --> 06:43.446
of shit who
gave her a concussion?

06:43.490 --> 06:46.797
- Yeah, his name is Ron.
- Oh, I know who he is.

06:46.841 --> 06:48.364
- That's him.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.366
Why is he not
in the back of your cruiser?

06:50.410 --> 06:53.325
- Victim insisted
it was an accident.

06:53.369 --> 06:55.980
- She has a kid, Paco.
Where is he?

06:56.024 --> 06:57.460
- I didn't see
any children in there.

06:57.504 --> 06:59.636
Probably for the best.

06:59.680 --> 07:02.639
[dramatic music]

07:02.683 --> 07:05.512
♪

07:05.555 --> 07:07.905
- Joe.

07:07.949 --> 07:09.690
You can't leave me in here.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.300
- I'm not--I'm not.
I'm sorry.

07:11.343 --> 07:13.520
Look, it's pointless to try
to explain anything to you

07:13.563 --> 07:16.348
without evidence,
so no more secrets.

07:16.392 --> 07:18.350
Ask me anything.

07:21.919 --> 07:23.878
So we both knew
Benji was a dick, right?

07:23.921 --> 07:25.706
What you didn't know...

07:25.749 --> 07:28.143
[keyboard clacking]

07:28.186 --> 07:31.233
He was a murderer.
He killed an innocent kid.

07:31.276 --> 07:33.191
- He's, he's playing dead.
He's playing dead.

07:33.235 --> 07:35.324
Oh, shit!
[camera fumbles]

07:36.368 --> 07:38.936
- No remorse, I fully maintain
he was sociopathic,

07:38.980 --> 07:41.112
and dangerous,
dangerous for you.

07:41.156 --> 07:44.507
And Peach, oh,
she was obsessed.

07:44.551 --> 07:46.683
And she was
hoarding these for years.

07:46.727 --> 07:49.904
She needed to own you, to trap
you, to make you her pet.

07:49.947 --> 07:53.124
And what happened
once she was gone?

07:53.168 --> 07:56.650
You blossomed,
you were published.

08:01.437 --> 08:06.137
I--I get why you'd be freaked,
all stuffed in like this.

08:06.181 --> 08:07.878
But they're just mementos,
you know?

08:07.922 --> 08:10.141
Like holding on
to an old photograph.

08:10.185 --> 08:12.970
Or you wearing
my shirt to sleep.

08:13.014 --> 08:14.363
You can't tell me
that's so crazy.

08:14.406 --> 08:16.974
It's the stuff
of a million love songs.

08:17.018 --> 08:18.541
I know this is a lot.

08:18.585 --> 08:19.803
Honestly, I'm terrified

08:19.847 --> 08:21.675
sharing this with you.

08:21.718 --> 08:23.372
But if we're being honest,

08:23.415 --> 08:25.113
your life has been better
since you met me.

08:25.156 --> 08:26.941
You just didn't
know how, or why.

08:26.984 --> 08:29.944
Until now.

08:29.987 --> 08:31.946
Beck, I love you.

08:31.989 --> 08:34.862
And loving someone means
you will do anything for them.

08:34.905 --> 08:37.865
[ominous music]

08:37.908 --> 08:45.176
♪

08:46.308 --> 08:48.049
Benji's.
- [exhales]

08:48.092 --> 08:50.138
- I had to burn his body.

08:51.618 --> 08:53.402
- And Peach?
- Well, she tried to kill me.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.230
That was
straight-up self defense.

08:55.273 --> 08:58.102
It was, it was self de--
- Oh, God.

08:58.146 --> 09:00.191
[sobbing] It's true.
- Please don't.

09:00.235 --> 09:02.629
- No, please!
- No, no, calm down, please.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.326
- Please don't hurt me!
- Please calm down.

09:04.369 --> 09:06.110
No, you don't understand.
Please calm down.

09:06.154 --> 09:07.634
- You killed them!
- Beck, Beck, Beck.

09:07.677 --> 09:10.767
- You're a murderer, you freak!
- No, that's not true!

09:10.811 --> 09:12.987
No, you haven't--
- Get away from me!

09:13.030 --> 09:14.466
Please don't hurt me.
- You don't understand.

09:14.510 --> 09:16.599
I would never
hurt someone I love.

09:16.643 --> 09:20.951
- Tell that to Candace,
you sick fuck!

09:20.995 --> 09:23.084
- You're not listening.

09:23.127 --> 09:26.087
[tense music]

09:26.130 --> 09:32.049
♪

09:32.093 --> 09:34.791
- [grunts]
Help!

09:34.835 --> 09:37.881
Help!

09:37.925 --> 09:42.625
Help!
Help me, please!

09:42.669 --> 09:44.018
Please!

09:47.804 --> 09:50.764
[soft music]

09:50.807 --> 09:58.119
♪

10:14.439 --> 10:16.224
- Good morning.
- [screams]

10:16.267 --> 10:19.009
Get away!
- It's okay.

10:22.447 --> 10:24.449
- What were you
trying to do to me?

10:24.493 --> 10:27.322
- I was just making it cozy.
Look.

10:27.365 --> 10:29.803
You were sleeping so deep,
I didn't want to disturb you.

10:29.846 --> 10:34.634
- Well, consider me disturbed.

10:39.160 --> 10:41.728
- Here,
I brought you breakfast.

10:41.771 --> 10:44.687
- Somehow, being inches
from a bucket of my own pee

10:44.731 --> 10:47.690
has killed my appetite.

10:47.734 --> 10:49.561
- Oh, well,
I emptied the bucket,

10:49.605 --> 10:52.477
in case you ever doubt what
I'm willing to do for love.

10:55.872 --> 10:59.833
And you're not going to
want to pass up avocado toast.

10:59.876 --> 11:05.926
From Dudley's, and uh, coffee.
Just how you like it.

11:05.969 --> 11:08.711
- I always wondered
what that was for.

11:08.755 --> 11:10.757
- Uh, oh, yeah.

11:10.800 --> 11:14.935
Mooney claims he built it
for secure cash transactions.

11:14.978 --> 11:17.938
I never saw anybody
down here but me.

11:17.981 --> 11:21.593
I spent a lot of time in here
when I was younger.

11:21.637 --> 11:23.770
I was always
getting into trouble.

11:23.813 --> 11:25.510
Mooney...

11:25.554 --> 11:27.730
he...

11:27.774 --> 11:29.297
he was my Mr. Miyagi.

11:29.340 --> 11:31.734
[tense music]

11:31.778 --> 11:33.910
If Miyagi was
a Soviet prison guard.

11:33.954 --> 11:37.044
- Who am I to you?
- You're an asshole.

11:37.087 --> 11:40.656
- Yes, but who else
do you have?

11:40.700 --> 11:43.920
Your father, who used
your armpit for an ashtray?

11:43.964 --> 11:46.096
Your mother, who never
did anything to stop him?

11:46.140 --> 11:49.926
Or maybe you miss that
insect ridden group home

11:49.970 --> 11:51.536
that drove you to my doorstep.

11:51.580 --> 11:54.365
- [scoffs]
You don't care about me.

11:54.409 --> 11:57.891
- This place could be
your salvation.

11:57.934 --> 11:59.980
Here...

12:00.023 --> 12:01.721
you're safe,

12:01.764 --> 12:04.941
surrounded by the
greatest works of humanity.

12:04.985 --> 12:10.555
- With no choice but to absorb
the wisdom of better men.

12:10.599 --> 12:12.732
Beck, in the end, the cage
was a good thing for me.

12:12.775 --> 12:14.516
I'm hoping it will
be the same for you.

12:14.559 --> 12:18.259
Look, look, hence, typewriter,
paper, no distractions.

12:20.870 --> 12:24.918
It's the low tech writer's
retreat you always wanted.

12:25.919 --> 12:28.922
- I feel bad for you, Joe.

12:28.965 --> 12:31.925
[soft music]

12:31.968 --> 12:34.014
♪

12:34.057 --> 12:37.017
- Was that pity?
Disgust?

12:37.060 --> 12:39.933
[door clanks shut]
Empathy?

12:39.976 --> 12:42.979
Beck, I am really
putting myself out there.

12:43.023 --> 12:44.546
The least you could do
is acknowledge that.

12:44.589 --> 12:47.375
- Hey, not today, little man.
Hey, look at me!

12:47.418 --> 12:48.942
Are you out of your mind?
What do you think you're doing?

12:48.985 --> 12:50.508
- Get your hands off him.
- Hey, I caught this punk

12:50.552 --> 12:51.814
trying to steal
the gun from the register.

12:51.858 --> 12:54.077
- Okay, okay, all right.
It's not loaded.

12:54.121 --> 12:56.166
Oh, it's loaded.
I'll handle it.

13:02.651 --> 13:05.480
This is not a toy.
- I know, I'm not dumb.

13:05.523 --> 13:07.090
- I think you are.
I think only an idiot

13:07.134 --> 13:08.352
tries what you just pulled.

13:08.396 --> 13:09.876
I know why you
want a gun, Paco.

13:09.919 --> 13:11.834
Even if you don't kill yourself
with this thing first,

13:11.878 --> 13:14.576
the second you use it
on Ron, your life is over.

13:14.619 --> 13:17.231
That is the definition of dumb.

13:18.536 --> 13:20.190
[gun thuds, drawer shuts]

13:24.107 --> 13:25.413
I'm sorry.

13:26.893 --> 13:29.025
I know that was harsh.

13:29.069 --> 13:30.984
[exhales]
It's a key to my place.

13:31.027 --> 13:32.768
You can go there, it's safe.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.075
Cool down, crash
as long as you need to.

13:35.118 --> 13:36.859
And we'll talk
about this later.

13:36.903 --> 13:39.862
[tense music]

13:39.906 --> 13:41.777
♪

13:41.821 --> 13:43.387
[cell phone dings]

13:46.129 --> 13:49.829
I'm not thinking straight,
and it's your fault.

13:49.872 --> 13:52.309
Beck, I can only
buy us so much time.

13:52.353 --> 13:54.659
And my patience
is wearing thin.

13:54.703 --> 13:56.226
- Joe, where have you been?
- Hey.

13:56.270 --> 13:58.272
- Whoo, hey.
- Let's skip the small talk.

13:58.315 --> 14:00.100
I just want to know
if Beck is okay.

14:00.143 --> 14:01.884
- Wait, what do you mean okay?
- We had a fight.

14:01.928 --> 14:04.539
I haven't heard from her.
- Oh, I think it's okay

14:04.582 --> 14:05.975
to tell you,
she's on a writing retreat.

14:06.019 --> 14:07.890
- Yeah.
[both laugh]

14:07.934 --> 14:11.415
- It's all good, relax.
- She's not texting us, either.

14:11.459 --> 14:12.634
- I just--I just want
to know she's safe.

14:12.677 --> 14:14.027
both: Yeah.
- [soft laugh]

14:14.070 --> 14:16.116
- What was the fight about?

14:16.159 --> 14:19.597
- Uh...

14:19.641 --> 14:20.903
[sighs]

14:20.947 --> 14:23.166
I caught her cheating
with her therapist.

14:23.210 --> 14:24.211
- No way.
- What?

14:24.254 --> 14:25.473
Oh, my God, no way.

14:25.516 --> 14:27.127
- Dr. Nicky?
Is she kidding?

14:27.170 --> 14:29.085
- Oh, my God. Whoa.
- Beck!

14:29.129 --> 14:31.000
- Joe, I am so sorry.
- Yeah.

14:31.044 --> 14:33.481
- So sorry.
- I'm so sorry, we had no idea.

14:33.524 --> 14:35.962
- I--I thought we could
work through it,

14:36.005 --> 14:38.138
but then, she ghosted me.

14:38.181 --> 14:39.617
- Wait, when she texted,

14:39.661 --> 14:40.967
she said that her retreat
was therapeutic.

14:41.010 --> 14:42.098
You don't think
that she's still--

14:42.142 --> 14:45.406
- I mean...yeah.

14:45.449 --> 14:48.931
- Wow.
- Wow.

14:48.975 --> 14:50.802
- [scoffs]

14:52.369 --> 14:54.806
I really thought
you two were endgame.

14:54.850 --> 14:57.331
It just kind of
shakes your faith, you know?

14:57.374 --> 14:58.941
I don't know.
- Do you really believe

14:58.985 --> 15:00.638
that Beck and I
are the real deal?

15:00.682 --> 15:05.382
- Joe, I've known Beck
a long time, and I have...

15:05.426 --> 15:07.080
I've never seen her happier.

15:07.123 --> 15:11.084
- Or like,
more grounded, or whatever.

15:11.127 --> 15:14.087
- I really think that you
bring out the best in her.

15:14.130 --> 15:17.090
- I think she brings out
the best in me, too.

15:17.133 --> 15:18.743
- Hey, maybe it's not so bad.

15:18.787 --> 15:20.963
Maybe--maybe she's really
on a writing retreat, you know?

15:21.007 --> 15:23.096
- Or maybe she's just
trying to dodge that P.I.

15:23.139 --> 15:24.575
because she doesn't
feel like talking about Peach.

15:24.619 --> 15:26.664
- P--wait, P.I.?
What do you mean?

15:26.708 --> 15:29.145
- Apparently, a Salinger
would never commit suicide,

15:29.189 --> 15:30.059
according to the Salingers.

15:30.103 --> 15:31.669
- It is so messed up.

15:31.713 --> 15:33.802
- They hired this guy,
I don't know.

15:33.845 --> 15:35.935
He's been asking Lynn and I
all of these questions.

15:35.978 --> 15:37.980
He even used
the term "foul play."

15:38.024 --> 15:40.156
Can you believe that?

15:40.200 --> 15:42.376
- Joe, we both know
what you did.

15:42.419 --> 15:44.552
Why are you surprised?

15:44.595 --> 15:47.555
[tense music]

15:47.598 --> 15:49.774
- I'm not going
to finish these.

15:49.818 --> 15:52.821
Any of these wontons,
you want them?

15:52.864 --> 15:54.692
- Okay.

15:58.914 --> 16:00.350
Thank you.

16:02.570 --> 16:06.922
- I recommend the ponzu.
The sweet and sour's too sour.

16:08.924 --> 16:10.447
- Noted.

16:14.669 --> 16:18.020
- You haven't started writing.

16:18.064 --> 16:19.152
- I'm still waiting for that

16:19.195 --> 16:22.503
surge of inspiration
I was promised.

16:24.809 --> 16:29.162
- You--you seem like you're
doing a little better.

16:29.205 --> 16:32.208
- [chuckles]

16:32.252 --> 16:35.211
Maybe it's relative.
- Mm.

16:37.083 --> 16:41.478
I caught Paco trying to steal
a gun from the register today.

16:41.522 --> 16:45.221
- What?
Why?

16:45.265 --> 16:47.267
- Ron put Claudia
in the hospital.

16:47.310 --> 16:51.575
So Paco, I tried
talking to him.

16:51.619 --> 16:55.144
I think I just
made him angrier.

16:55.188 --> 16:58.321
- Well, you got your girlfriend
locked up in a cage.

16:58.365 --> 17:02.151
A P.I.'s snooping around,

17:02.195 --> 17:04.414
and you're worried
about your neighbor's kid.

17:04.458 --> 17:10.029
- I know, it's pretty dumb.
- No.

17:10.072 --> 17:11.247
It's sweet.

17:11.291 --> 17:14.250
[ambient music]

17:14.294 --> 17:16.078
♪

17:16.122 --> 17:18.167
Joe.

17:19.821 --> 17:22.084
I know...

17:22.128 --> 17:25.522
there is a good heart
in there somewhere.

17:32.007 --> 17:34.314
Joe?

17:34.357 --> 17:36.142
- Yeah?

17:38.579 --> 17:40.929
- I have to pee.

17:47.936 --> 17:50.025
- Oh, no, no,
tell me you're not using

17:50.069 --> 17:53.289
Henry Pelham's cartography
as a seat cover.

17:53.333 --> 17:55.813
- Sorry, I couldn't
find any Dan Brown.

17:55.857 --> 17:57.815
- All right,
I'll get out of here.

17:57.859 --> 17:59.295
- Joe.

18:02.124 --> 18:05.040
Can I--can I just,

18:05.084 --> 18:08.478
please use the bathroom?

18:08.522 --> 18:13.483
Please, this is dehumanizing.

18:13.527 --> 18:16.269
You can trust me.

18:36.811 --> 18:38.204
Thank you.

18:38.247 --> 18:41.337
Thank you, thank you, thank
you, thank you, thank you.

18:41.381 --> 18:44.340
[gentle music]

18:44.384 --> 18:51.434
♪

18:59.529 --> 19:03.142
Joe--
- I can't.

19:03.185 --> 19:05.796
I'm sorry.

19:05.840 --> 19:08.495
- Joe.

19:08.538 --> 19:12.281
Joe, please!
- I'll be back in a little bit.

19:12.325 --> 19:15.328
- Shit, shit, shit, shit.

19:15.371 --> 19:18.766
[exhales]
I'm so stupid.

19:18.809 --> 19:24.206
This whole time, I was wrong.

19:24.250 --> 19:27.296
How did I not see this?
- If you see this place

19:27.340 --> 19:30.038
as a prison, that's all
you're going to be, a prisoner.

19:30.081 --> 19:32.954
If you see it as an
opportunity for introspection,

19:32.997 --> 19:38.307
and growth, voila,
we have a future together.

19:38.351 --> 19:40.570
You say you're a writer.

19:40.614 --> 19:43.269
I fell in love with a writer.

19:43.312 --> 19:46.489
Maybe you should be writing.

19:46.533 --> 19:49.100
- Well, what now, Joe?

19:49.144 --> 19:52.321
You're going to go
jerk off to my panties?

19:52.365 --> 19:56.412
Or do you need to cut someone
up before you can get hard?

19:56.456 --> 19:58.066
[yells]

19:58.109 --> 20:01.069
[dramatic music]

20:01.112 --> 20:08.163
♪

20:19.392 --> 20:21.611
- How the hell
did you end up here?

20:21.655 --> 20:25.093
[tense music]

20:25.136 --> 20:26.747
- Your life has been better
since you met me.

20:26.790 --> 20:28.270
You just didn't know
how or why.

20:28.314 --> 20:30.272
You paint me up
to be this monster.

20:30.316 --> 20:33.362
Someone who can hurt people,
who can do terrible things.

20:33.406 --> 20:34.972
♪

20:35.016 --> 20:37.323
[typewriter clacking echoes]

20:37.366 --> 20:42.066
You used to wrap yourself
in fairy tales like a blanket.

20:42.110 --> 20:45.200
But it was the cold you loved.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.202
Sharp shivers as you uncovered

20:47.246 --> 20:50.423
the corpses
of Bluebeard's wives.

20:50.466 --> 20:52.903
Sweeter goose bumps
as Prince Charming

20:52.947 --> 20:55.776
slid one glass slipper
over your little toes,

20:55.819 --> 20:57.517
a perfect fit.

20:57.560 --> 20:59.867
♪

20:59.910 --> 21:02.086
But by the schoolyard,
real princesses

21:02.130 --> 21:04.785
floated by you on fall winds.

21:04.828 --> 21:07.396
You saw the gulf between
you and the rich girls,

21:07.440 --> 21:11.313
and vowed to stop
believing in fairy tales.

21:11.357 --> 21:15.274
But the stories
were in you, deep as poison.

21:15.317 --> 21:18.538
If Prince Charming was real,
if he could save you--

21:18.581 --> 21:23.325
you needed to be saved from
the unfairness of everything--

21:23.369 --> 21:26.285
when would he come?

21:26.328 --> 21:30.463
The answer was a cruel shrug
in a hundred fleeting moments.

21:30.506 --> 21:33.074
The sneer
on Stevie Smith's face

21:33.117 --> 21:35.163
when he called you a fat cow.

21:35.206 --> 21:37.687
Uncle Jeff's hand
squeezing your ass

21:37.731 --> 21:39.341
in the Thanksgiving kitchen.

21:39.385 --> 21:42.431
The accusation
in your father's eyes

21:42.475 --> 21:44.912
when you told him
what happened.

21:44.955 --> 21:47.523
[typewriter clacking echoes]

21:47.567 --> 21:50.657
From every boy masquerading
as a man that you let

21:50.700 --> 21:54.487
into your body, your heart,
you learned you didn't have

21:54.530 --> 21:59.448
whatever magic
turns a beast into a prince.

21:59.492 --> 22:00.841
You surrounded yourself

22:00.884 --> 22:04.192
with the girls
you'd always resented,

22:04.235 --> 22:07.717
hoping to share their power,
and you hated yourself.

22:07.761 --> 22:11.199
And that
diminished you even more.

22:11.242 --> 22:13.375
And then,
right when you thought

22:13.419 --> 22:18.380
you might just disappear,
he saw you.

22:19.250 --> 22:22.036
And you knew, somewhere deep,
it was too good to be true.

22:22.079 --> 22:24.081
But you let yourself be swept,

22:24.125 --> 22:28.042
because he was the first
strong enough to lift you.

22:28.085 --> 22:30.827
Now, in his castle,
you understand Prince Charming

22:30.871 --> 22:34.309
and Bluebeard
are the same man.

22:34.353 --> 22:39.793
And you don't get a happy end
unless you love both of him.

22:39.836 --> 22:42.491
Didn't you want this?
To be loved?

22:42.535 --> 22:44.493
Didn't you want him
to crown you?

22:44.537 --> 22:47.409
Didn't you ask for it?
Didn't you ask for it?

22:47.453 --> 22:49.629
Didn't you ask for it?

22:49.672 --> 22:51.674
So say you can live like this.

22:51.718 --> 22:53.850
Say you love him,
say thank you,

22:53.894 --> 22:56.157
say anything but the truth.

22:56.200 --> 22:59.203
What if you
can't love him back?

23:02.119 --> 23:04.992
- What if you're not the one?

23:05.035 --> 23:10.258
No, now is not the time
to abandon principles.

23:10.301 --> 23:13.566
I have to believe
love conquers all.

23:13.609 --> 23:18.745
And if you love me,
it's only a matter of time.

23:18.788 --> 23:22.575
But time is not on our side.

23:22.618 --> 23:25.447
[tense music]

23:25.491 --> 23:29.146
I don't want
to think worst case.

23:29.190 --> 23:31.366
I don't like
having to scour your place

23:31.410 --> 23:34.500
for evidence that'd
link me to your disappearance.

23:34.543 --> 23:38.025
It's all starting
to feel a little dirty.

23:38.068 --> 23:41.594
Because I'm not
doing it for you anymore.

23:41.637 --> 23:44.553
I'm doing it for me.

23:44.597 --> 23:48.383
And I'm not a selfish person.

23:48.427 --> 23:51.125
[tense music]

23:51.168 --> 23:55.216
You said you believe
I have a good heart somewhere.

23:55.259 --> 23:58.654
I hope you don't mind if I
take a minute to look for it.

23:58.698 --> 24:01.178
Claudia.

24:01.222 --> 24:04.530
- Joe, what are you doing here?
- I'm looking for Paco.

24:04.573 --> 24:06.793
Is Ron around?
- No.

24:06.836 --> 24:09.622
And I was hoping
that Paco went to find you.

24:09.665 --> 24:12.363
I lost my cell phone when...

24:12.407 --> 24:14.583
The nurses said they tried
calling the apartment,

24:14.627 --> 24:15.497
but nobody answered.

24:15.541 --> 24:16.803
- So you--you have no idea

24:16.846 --> 24:19.545
where your son is?

24:19.588 --> 24:22.025
Jesus, Claudia.
- [sighs]

24:22.069 --> 24:24.680
So damn easy to judge, huh?
Who the hell are you?

24:24.724 --> 24:26.465
- I'm the only one in this city

24:26.508 --> 24:28.641
who cares about
your son, apparently.

24:28.684 --> 24:30.947
Why do you do this?
Why do you protect the man

24:30.991 --> 24:33.123
who does this to you
over your child?

24:33.167 --> 24:34.821
Over and over.
You're his mother.

24:34.864 --> 24:37.693
Mothers are supposed
to protect their children

24:37.737 --> 24:40.435
from men like him.
- I don't need a concerned

24:40.479 --> 24:42.655
neighbor bursting
in here and blaming me

24:42.698 --> 24:44.526
for my own concussion.

24:44.570 --> 24:47.007
[tense music]

24:47.050 --> 24:50.358
Ron has connections.
He's made threats.

24:50.401 --> 24:54.231
You want to know why
he's still in the picture?

24:54.275 --> 24:58.366
I stand up to him,
I lose my boy.

25:02.152 --> 25:04.894
- I'm sorry,
I didn't know that.

25:04.938 --> 25:07.201
- Yeah, of course you didn't.

25:07.244 --> 25:10.509
You have no idea
what it takes to live my life.

25:10.552 --> 25:13.773
They don't write books
about women like me.

25:13.816 --> 25:15.644
No one would think to.

25:15.688 --> 25:19.735
♪

25:19.779 --> 25:23.565
[distant sirens wailing]

25:23.609 --> 25:25.567
- Joe Goldberg.

25:28.222 --> 25:30.485
- Hello, P.I.
Have we met?

25:30.529 --> 25:32.531
- Hi, I work for the family
of Peach Salinger.

25:32.574 --> 25:34.402
Just a couple
of quick questions.

25:34.445 --> 25:37.448
- Oh, okay, sure, of course.
- How well did you know Peach?

25:37.492 --> 25:39.494
- He's asking,
but he knows already.

25:39.538 --> 25:42.323
Not well, through my ex,
Guinevere Beck.

25:42.366 --> 25:44.325
Well enough to
be saddened by her passing.

25:44.368 --> 25:46.022
- You been to
her house in Greenwich?

25:46.066 --> 25:49.199
- That's where she died, right?
No, no.

25:49.243 --> 25:50.592
I heard about it through Beck.

25:50.636 --> 25:51.985
I know that Peach
was having a hard time

25:52.028 --> 25:53.464
when they were out there.

25:53.508 --> 25:55.249
Um...yeah.

25:55.292 --> 25:56.729
I think you should
talk to Beck.

25:56.772 --> 25:59.732
- I've been trying to get
a hold of Beck, actually.

25:59.775 --> 26:03.692
- Yeah, well, we--we broke up.
[chuckles]

26:03.736 --> 26:06.216
So I'm not really in touch.

26:06.260 --> 26:07.522
In fact, if you found me,
that means

26:07.566 --> 26:09.393
you probably found Lynn,
Beck's friend.

26:09.437 --> 26:12.745
She's the one to ask.
Beck, she might be out of town.

26:12.788 --> 26:15.922
Writing, she does that, so.

26:15.965 --> 26:17.314
Good luck.
It was nice to meet you.

26:17.358 --> 26:18.881
- You spend a lot of time
at her place

26:18.925 --> 26:20.753
when she's out of town?

26:20.796 --> 26:21.971
- Shit.

26:22.015 --> 26:23.886
Well, I--
He saw me.

26:23.930 --> 26:25.627
I--I still have a key.

26:25.671 --> 26:27.629
No--in fact, I had a key.

26:27.673 --> 26:28.674
I returned it last night.

26:28.717 --> 26:31.590
[suspenseful music]

26:31.633 --> 26:33.635
Should I be worried?
Are you following me?

26:33.679 --> 26:36.725
- Did your ex ever tell you
that Peach had a stalker?

26:36.769 --> 26:38.640
- I mean, I know, um...

26:38.684 --> 26:41.251
I remember the awful
Central Park incident.

26:41.295 --> 26:42.688
Peach was attacked, right?

26:42.731 --> 26:44.690
But I wasn't aware
it was anything

26:44.733 --> 26:45.865
more than a random robbery.

26:45.908 --> 26:46.953
- Same individual may have been

26:46.996 --> 26:49.085
in the house
the weekend Peach died.

26:49.129 --> 26:51.827
- Seriously?
- Found an item.

26:51.871 --> 26:55.091
We're testing it for DNA now.
- Wow.

26:57.572 --> 26:59.008
That would be crazy.

26:59.052 --> 27:01.141
I forgot the goddamn jar.

27:01.184 --> 27:04.187
Well, if it's true,
I hope you find the guy.

27:04.231 --> 27:06.625
I should have pissed myself.

27:06.668 --> 27:08.888
Let me know
if there's anything I can do.

27:08.931 --> 27:10.324
- Thanks, Joe.

27:10.367 --> 27:13.719
You mind calling if you
think of anything else?

27:13.762 --> 27:15.285
- Yeah.

27:15.329 --> 27:17.113
But does urine even hold DNA?

27:17.157 --> 27:19.725
Will do, Ross, yeah.

27:19.768 --> 27:23.163
One thing I learned from my
own time in the cage, Beck.

27:23.206 --> 27:25.731
Never let yourself panic.

27:25.774 --> 27:28.603
No matter how bad it is,
you find a way

27:28.647 --> 27:31.127
to stay calm,
and keep your wits.

27:36.132 --> 27:39.092
[soft music]

27:39.135 --> 27:46.447
♪

27:50.364 --> 27:55.456
- I've been stupid to be mad.
I messed up.

27:55.499 --> 27:59.634
And you're trying
to help me do better.

27:59.678 --> 28:02.681
- I know it's hard
to understand.

28:02.724 --> 28:05.118
But sometimes,
we do difficult things

28:05.161 --> 28:07.294
out of caring for someone.

28:13.909 --> 28:16.956
I know the demons
that drive you.

28:16.999 --> 28:19.828
I have them, too.

28:19.872 --> 28:23.484
It takes discipline...

28:23.527 --> 28:25.704
to prevail.

28:25.747 --> 28:30.578
That's why I work you so hard,
why I demand perfection.

28:30.621 --> 28:32.841
My love for the books, respect.

28:32.885 --> 28:36.149
I'm trying to teach you
a code to live by so that

28:36.192 --> 28:38.891
you don't end up
like your father.

28:38.934 --> 28:41.589
- And when I fail,
you lock me in.

28:41.632 --> 28:43.809
- Exactly.

28:43.852 --> 28:46.202
Because I love you.

28:46.246 --> 28:48.465
I only hope it will be enough.

28:48.509 --> 28:50.076
- Hey.

28:53.209 --> 28:55.255
Hey, I'm sorry that I--

28:55.298 --> 28:58.214
that I went a little crazy
before.

29:01.827 --> 29:03.654
What's for dinner?

29:10.052 --> 29:12.272
[ambient music]

29:12.315 --> 29:14.013
♪

29:14.056 --> 29:17.146
What's wrong?
What happened?

29:17.190 --> 29:20.497
- Remember the P.I.?
He paid a visit.

29:20.541 --> 29:22.456
You should have seen him.

29:22.499 --> 29:25.241
I don't think
he bought a word I said.

29:25.285 --> 29:31.987
♪

29:32.031 --> 29:34.773
I'm not a killer.

29:34.816 --> 29:37.166
I didn't plan this.

29:37.210 --> 29:40.387
Like, if I was
some premeditated,

29:40.430 --> 29:42.215
cold-blooded monster,
I wouldn't have missed

29:42.258 --> 29:43.477
anything that
would come back to

29:43.520 --> 29:46.828
bite me in the ass like this.

29:46.872 --> 29:49.483
- What did you miss?

29:49.526 --> 29:51.006
- It doesn't matter,
unless it does.

29:51.050 --> 29:54.096
In which case, you'll know,
because I'll go to prison.

29:54.140 --> 29:56.751
You might get
exactly what you want.

29:56.795 --> 29:59.885
I'll go down for
something I did for you.

29:59.928 --> 30:01.408
And you love that, right?

30:01.451 --> 30:03.976
I mean that's--
that's what you think of me.

30:05.716 --> 30:07.849
- No.

30:07.893 --> 30:10.373
That's not true.

30:10.417 --> 30:12.593
You're not a monster, Joe.

30:12.636 --> 30:15.117
I know--
I know I've said some stuff,

30:15.161 --> 30:18.729
but come on, you can't
expect me to be chill.

30:18.773 --> 30:20.688
I mean, look at us.

30:22.733 --> 30:25.736
For the record...

30:25.780 --> 30:27.826
I don't hate you.

30:30.176 --> 30:35.964
I am trying so hard
to understand you.

30:36.008 --> 30:39.881
And can you blame me if I need
a little help getting there?

30:44.973 --> 30:47.280
And what about Paco?

30:47.323 --> 30:48.803
- What about Paco?

30:48.847 --> 30:50.979
- If you go to jail,
the kid is screwed, right?

30:51.023 --> 30:52.894
You think that's what I want?

30:52.938 --> 30:55.549
You're the only person
who is there for him.

30:55.592 --> 30:57.507
And I think about what happens

30:57.551 --> 31:01.947
to people who
don't have anyone.

31:01.990 --> 31:05.124
Joe, for Paco, okay?

31:05.167 --> 31:07.909
Let's try and figure out
a way through this,

31:07.953 --> 31:10.999
so that you can--

31:12.958 --> 31:17.919
so that we
can be there for him.

31:17.963 --> 31:19.703
[knocking]

31:19.747 --> 31:21.444
- Claudia?

31:21.488 --> 31:22.837
Just open the door, I want--

31:22.881 --> 31:25.013
I just want
to talk to you, just--

31:25.057 --> 31:26.667
[knocking]

31:26.710 --> 31:29.017
Hey, let me in.
I just want...

31:29.061 --> 31:30.584
[dramatic music]

31:30.627 --> 31:32.238
- [yells]
- [grunts]

31:32.281 --> 31:33.239
[body thuds]

31:33.282 --> 31:34.327
[weapon clatters]

31:34.370 --> 31:41.682
♪

31:44.380 --> 31:46.948
You piece of shit!

31:46.992 --> 31:49.951
[dramatic ambient music]

31:49.995 --> 31:57.306
♪

32:05.010 --> 32:06.750
Paco.

32:10.972 --> 32:15.324
Paco, come here,
I want to talk to you.

32:15.368 --> 32:16.978
Paco, come here.

32:17.022 --> 32:19.546
I'm not--
I'm not going to hurt you.

32:30.252 --> 32:31.645
- Paco?

32:31.688 --> 32:33.038
- Paco, get over here,

32:33.081 --> 32:36.215
I want to talk to you.

32:36.258 --> 32:37.607
Ah--

32:37.651 --> 32:40.871
[suspenseful music]

32:40.915 --> 32:42.482
♪

32:42.525 --> 32:45.398
Paco, come out here.

32:45.441 --> 32:47.443
- [gasps]

32:50.055 --> 32:51.882
- You're dead.

32:51.926 --> 32:53.884
- Hey, Ron.

32:56.800 --> 32:59.847
[grunts]
- [chokes, gurgles]

32:59.890 --> 33:02.067
[coughs]

33:06.375 --> 33:09.030
- Joe!
- Paco.

33:09.074 --> 33:12.033
[stirring music]

33:12.077 --> 33:17.169
♪

33:20.433 --> 33:22.087
Okay, this is what
I need you to do

33:22.130 --> 33:26.134
so no one finds out about this,
because people are not really

33:26.178 --> 33:28.354
going to believe us about the
way that it happened, right?

33:28.397 --> 33:30.051
Okay, there's
blood in the hall.

33:30.095 --> 33:32.184
You need to clean that up
with soap and water.

33:32.227 --> 33:34.142
And then hit those spots
with bleach, really pour it on.

33:34.186 --> 33:36.318
All right, now this next part
might sound a little weird,

33:36.362 --> 33:39.147
but I think
it might do the trick.

33:39.191 --> 33:40.757
You see this, it's Ron's phone.

33:40.801 --> 33:44.152
I'm going to be texting
your mom from it.

33:44.196 --> 33:48.200
Maybe Ron's boss,
a few of his friends.

33:48.243 --> 33:49.810
- So they think
he's still alive.

33:49.853 --> 33:52.508
- Exactly, so I'm going
to keep that going.

33:52.552 --> 33:54.858
I'm going to take it far away
from here, get rid of it.

33:54.902 --> 33:59.646
All you have to do is say
you don't know where he is.

34:03.345 --> 34:05.217
Shit.

34:08.176 --> 34:11.701
Ron will never
hurt or scare you

34:11.745 --> 34:14.269
or your mom ever again,
and I'm sorry.

34:14.313 --> 34:16.184
I'm so sorry you
had to see that,

34:16.228 --> 34:17.881
but it's over.

34:19.840 --> 34:23.148
It's all over now, forever.
Right?

34:23.191 --> 34:27.282
- He was a bad man.
- [exhales] Yeah.

34:29.154 --> 34:31.330
He was.

34:31.373 --> 34:33.897
- Does that mean
it was right to kill him?

34:36.378 --> 34:38.859
- Sometimes...

34:38.902 --> 34:43.255
we do bad things
for the people we love.

34:43.298 --> 34:44.430
It doesn't mean it's right.

34:44.473 --> 34:47.563
It means love
is more important.

34:50.088 --> 34:52.090
All right, go on.

34:52.133 --> 34:55.745
I believe that, Beck.
Love is more important.

34:55.789 --> 34:58.444
But the world
is a cruel place.

34:58.487 --> 35:00.141
If I get caught
for any of this,

35:00.185 --> 35:03.188
I doubt a jury will
see it the same way.

35:03.231 --> 35:06.060
And you.
[typewriter clacking]

35:06.104 --> 35:08.193
Will you?

35:08.236 --> 35:10.325
- There you are.

35:14.199 --> 35:16.070
Read this, Joe.

35:22.032 --> 35:24.992
[ambient music]

35:25.035 --> 35:31.041
♪

35:31.085 --> 35:34.480
- A blind verse rendition of
your love story with Dr. Nicky?

35:34.523 --> 35:37.091
- Keep reading.

35:46.405 --> 35:48.581
- What exactly is this?

35:48.624 --> 35:51.758
- It's the story
of everything that happened

35:51.801 --> 35:56.241
once I started having an
affair with my therapist.

35:56.284 --> 35:59.505
I was broken, and trusting,
and I needed help.

35:59.548 --> 36:03.030
And he, little did I know,
he was obsessive,

36:03.073 --> 36:06.860
and very sick, and would stop
at nothing to get closer to me.

36:06.903 --> 36:10.298
And if you skip to the end,
there's this part

36:10.342 --> 36:12.257
where I talk about
a box of mementos

36:12.300 --> 36:15.434
that I found on
Nicky's property, evidence.

36:15.477 --> 36:19.264
A jar of teeth.

36:19.307 --> 36:22.441
Joe, don't you see?

36:22.484 --> 36:25.052
Nicky is your way out, Joe.

36:25.095 --> 36:28.142
Our way out.

36:28.186 --> 36:30.188
It's perfect.

36:33.147 --> 36:34.627
I get it now.

36:34.670 --> 36:36.716
- You get what?
- You.

36:36.759 --> 36:39.501
You did everything...

36:39.545 --> 36:41.155
for me.

36:41.199 --> 36:45.159
No one has ever loved me
the way that you love me.

36:45.203 --> 36:51.252
I mean, you--
you gave me everything.

36:51.296 --> 36:55.256
Let me give this to you.

36:55.300 --> 36:57.084
I mean it.

36:57.127 --> 36:59.173
I understand.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.043
I was scared.

37:00.087 --> 37:01.871
I could have done something--

37:01.915 --> 37:04.700
something really stupid
when I found that box,

37:04.744 --> 37:08.661
But this, this...

37:08.704 --> 37:10.315
gave me time to think.

37:10.358 --> 37:12.969
- I hurt you.
I scared you.

37:13.013 --> 37:17.800
I understand if you hate me.

37:17.844 --> 37:22.370
- I love you, actually.

37:22.414 --> 37:23.763
More than ever.

37:23.806 --> 37:26.461
And I can wait
until you're ready.

37:26.505 --> 37:29.508
It's not so bad in here.

37:29.551 --> 37:34.295
You take care of me,
and no one has ever

37:34.339 --> 37:36.515
taken care of me before,

37:36.558 --> 37:38.430
not like you.

37:38.473 --> 37:41.346
- It's all I ever wanted to do.

37:41.389 --> 37:42.390
- And when you're ready,

37:42.434 --> 37:44.349
we can take my story public.

37:44.392 --> 37:47.961
And then, you and I, we can go
somewhere and start our life.

37:48.004 --> 37:53.009
And--and I--I haven't,
I haven't thought beyond that,

37:53.053 --> 37:56.012
but Joe, I...

37:56.056 --> 38:01.409
I know that I am better
with you than without you.

38:01.453 --> 38:04.194
- [whispers]
Beck...

38:04.238 --> 38:06.719
- Oh, if you were in here, this
would be our moment to kiss.

38:06.762 --> 38:10.592
It's like, the music swells
and everything.

38:10.636 --> 38:13.595
[orchestral music swelling]

38:13.639 --> 38:14.640
♪

38:14.683 --> 38:17.033
But I know...

38:17.077 --> 38:20.123
I know you don't
trust me enough yet.

38:20.167 --> 38:21.690
I get it.

38:24.389 --> 38:26.826
[exhales]
Oh, we're crazy.

38:37.402 --> 38:39.621
[keys jingling]

38:39.665 --> 38:42.363
[lock clicks, turns]

38:58.727 --> 39:03.384
[ambient tone]

39:03.428 --> 39:06.300
[ominous music]

39:06.344 --> 39:09.521
♪

39:09.564 --> 39:11.349
[both grunt]

39:11.392 --> 39:12.350
- [groans]

39:12.393 --> 39:13.438
[dramatic music]

39:13.481 --> 39:15.396
[groans]

39:15.440 --> 39:16.876
Beck!

39:23.535 --> 39:24.971
- Wait, wait, wait, please.

39:25.014 --> 39:26.581
Wait--I know--
I know you're angry, I know.

39:26.625 --> 39:29.410
- You have no idea what I am,
you fucking psychopath!

39:29.454 --> 39:31.412
- I knew it was
too good to be true.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.545
- What, all the
nice things I said to you

39:33.588 --> 39:36.069
while I was locked in a cage?

39:36.112 --> 39:39.899
You actually believe that all
of this is somehow justified?

39:39.942 --> 39:43.206
- It is.
- Fuck, you are insane.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.078
You think that
you did some bad shit,

39:45.121 --> 39:46.471
and that I did some bad shit,

39:46.514 --> 39:49.604
and that this--
this is equivalent?

39:49.648 --> 39:52.433
Yeah, I lied, I cheated,

39:52.477 --> 39:54.827
but I--I didn't stalk you.

39:54.870 --> 39:58.657
I didn't hit you.
I didn't kill people.

39:58.700 --> 39:59.701
I didn't do any of this!

39:59.745 --> 40:01.224
- There's not a line

40:01.268 --> 40:04.097
in the world
that I wouldn't cross for you.

40:04.140 --> 40:06.665
- I didn't ask you
to swoop in for me.

40:06.708 --> 40:07.753
- But you did,
your life was a mess.

40:07.796 --> 40:09.537
- Yes, but it was my life.

40:09.581 --> 40:13.628
And I didn't need some
sociopath on a white horse

40:13.672 --> 40:15.021
to clean house.

40:15.064 --> 40:16.892
I mean,
what gives you the right?

40:16.936 --> 40:20.287
You thought that
I would be grateful?

40:20.330 --> 40:23.246
[exhales]

40:23.290 --> 40:25.597
You.

40:25.640 --> 40:28.121
You're him.

40:28.164 --> 40:30.210
You are the bad thing.

40:30.253 --> 40:33.648
You are the thing
that you should have killed.

40:33.692 --> 40:36.216
- If you let me out...

40:36.259 --> 40:38.000
we can just talk--
- You know what I think?

40:38.044 --> 40:41.961
I think that this was
all just an excuse.

40:42.004 --> 40:45.312
An excuse to justify
creeping into girls' lives,

40:45.355 --> 40:48.358
and violating
the shit out of them.

40:48.402 --> 40:49.534
I think you love it!

40:49.577 --> 40:52.537
The power, you love it!
- No, I don't.

40:52.580 --> 40:54.234
- I think that this, this was

40:54.277 --> 40:57.455
the perfect excuse
to take out people, like--

40:57.498 --> 40:59.544
like Benji, and Peach,

40:59.587 --> 41:00.719
who have always
looked down on you

41:00.762 --> 41:03.373
and your whole miserable life.

41:03.417 --> 41:06.638
God, but you--
you are not special.

41:06.681 --> 41:08.683
You're broken.

41:08.727 --> 41:11.033
I could never love you.

41:13.383 --> 41:17.562
Rot in there,
you psychotic asshole.

41:17.605 --> 41:21.566
You're going to spend
the rest of your life in jail.

41:32.794 --> 41:34.535
- Joe?

41:35.667 --> 41:38.626
[dramatic music]

41:38.670 --> 41:43.152
♪

41:43.196 --> 41:46.504
- [grunts]
Help!

41:46.547 --> 41:48.462
[muffled]
Help!

41:48.506 --> 41:51.552
Help!

41:51.596 --> 41:52.771
Paco.

41:52.814 --> 41:54.120
Paco, thank God.
I need your help.

41:54.163 --> 41:55.425
Open this door right now.

41:55.469 --> 41:59.081
Joe, he is downstairs,
and he's crazy.

41:59.125 --> 42:00.822
- Joe?
- Paco.

42:00.866 --> 42:03.608
He has killed people.
He's going to kill me.

42:03.651 --> 42:06.262
Open this door right now.

42:06.306 --> 42:11.006
Paco, open the door!
Open the door, please!

42:11.050 --> 42:14.532
Please, Paco, no!
No, Paco!

42:14.575 --> 42:16.664
[muffled screams]

42:18.666 --> 42:20.668
Keys, keys.

42:31.549 --> 42:33.594
[gasps]

42:33.638 --> 42:35.683
- When Mooney locked me in,
I learned a big lesson.

42:35.727 --> 42:39.557
Hide a spare key so you can
get out of the goddamn cage.

42:41.994 --> 42:44.387
I didn't want it
to be like this, Beck.

42:44.431 --> 42:46.651
- I know.

42:46.694 --> 42:49.175
I know, just...

42:49.218 --> 42:51.394
put me back in there.

42:53.614 --> 42:56.574
[dramatic music]

42:56.617 --> 43:03.624
♪

43:31.739 --> 43:32.784
[screams]

43:36.918 --> 43:38.616
[indistinct chatter]

43:38.659 --> 43:40.966
- These have been
selling like crazy.

43:41.009 --> 43:42.532
- Is it true she worked here?

43:42.576 --> 43:44.360
- Uh, yeah, it's true.
I knew her well.

43:44.404 --> 43:46.754
- I'm so sorry.
It's really tragic.

43:46.798 --> 43:48.669
- It's pretty weird when
someone dies,

43:48.713 --> 43:51.803
and you literally can't
get away from them on the news.

43:51.846 --> 43:54.719
Enjoy the book.
She was a really good writer.

43:54.762 --> 43:57.809
- You really were, Beck.

43:57.852 --> 44:01.029
I miss you so much.

44:01.073 --> 44:03.118
It's been a weird four months.

44:03.162 --> 44:06.382
I had to do a lot
for you, in the end.

44:06.426 --> 44:08.384
[somber alternative rock
music]

44:08.428 --> 44:10.952
- ♪ I need my girl

44:10.996 --> 44:13.781
♪

44:13.825 --> 44:20.353
♪ I need my girl

44:20.396 --> 44:22.311
- You wrote the story.

44:22.355 --> 44:25.793
All I did was
bring it to life.

44:25.837 --> 44:27.839
The story was perfect.

44:27.882 --> 44:30.842
So everyone believed it.

44:30.885 --> 44:35.542
- ♪ I need my girl

44:35.585 --> 44:37.892
- Doctor, Doctor!
[indistinct clamoring]

44:37.936 --> 44:39.764
What drove you
to murder Guinevere Beck?

44:39.807 --> 44:41.853
- Yes, she was definitely
having an affair

44:41.896 --> 44:42.854
with her therapist.

44:42.897 --> 44:44.116
- That evil [bleep].

44:44.159 --> 44:45.595
You know her friend,
Peach Salinger,

44:45.639 --> 44:47.336
was trying to get Beck
to stop seeing him,

44:47.380 --> 44:49.991
so it's like, did that
psycho kill Peach, too?

44:50.035 --> 44:51.863
- I received the
manuscript in the mail.

44:51.906 --> 44:55.431
It was odd, but far and away
the most moving prose I'd read

44:55.475 --> 44:56.868
since Zadie's second to last.

44:56.911 --> 44:58.739
It was also the most horrifying

44:58.783 --> 45:02.482
because I came to understand
that Beck was illuminating

45:02.525 --> 45:05.180
her very own imminent murder.

45:05.224 --> 45:06.878
That's when I knew.

45:06.921 --> 45:10.882
I had to show it to
my literary agent right away.

45:10.925 --> 45:12.361
- It's true,
maybe not everyone

45:12.405 --> 45:13.711
was completely convinced.

45:13.754 --> 45:15.321
- Bullshit.

45:15.364 --> 45:17.540
- But you know what,
doesn't matter.

45:17.584 --> 45:19.629
The evidence was overwhelming.

45:19.673 --> 45:23.808
Thanks to your
hard work, and mine.

45:23.851 --> 45:27.942
It's the last thing
we ever did together.

45:27.986 --> 45:30.640
In the end,
you couldn't love me.

45:30.684 --> 45:33.992
I feel at peace with that now,
because I loved you

45:34.035 --> 45:36.516
the absolute best
that I could.

45:36.559 --> 45:38.605
And I gave you
what you wanted.

45:38.648 --> 45:40.825
I feel good about that.
I helped you become

45:40.868 --> 45:42.827
the writer
you so wanted to be.

45:42.870 --> 45:46.526
Your lurid memoir
of Dr. Nicky was the lede,

45:46.569 --> 45:48.397
but I cobbled
that manuscript together

45:48.441 --> 45:50.965
from every one of
your pieces fit to print.

45:51.009 --> 45:54.839
The book is yours, Beck,
and it made you famous.

45:54.882 --> 45:59.017
It's sad you're
not here to see it.

45:59.060 --> 46:02.934
But I know
you would be so happy.

46:02.977 --> 46:08.417
♪

46:11.856 --> 46:16.512
- So, California.
- Yeah, that's great, you know?

46:16.556 --> 46:18.079
You got the job.
Paco's going to love it.

46:18.123 --> 46:22.518
- Yeah, I think so.
Weather's so good.

46:22.562 --> 46:26.827
- So, Ron?
- Disappeared into thin air.

46:26.871 --> 46:28.786
I don't get it, but

46:28.829 --> 46:31.049
you know, everyone knew
he was a troubled guy.

46:31.092 --> 46:32.267
He had gambling debts,
who knows.

46:32.311 --> 46:34.792
It's for the best.

46:34.835 --> 46:37.838
I know I haven't always
been the nicest about it,

46:37.882 --> 46:39.666
but, uh...

46:39.709 --> 46:41.842
thanks for always
being so good to my son.

46:41.886 --> 46:45.063
- [scoffs]
That's--it's nothing.

46:45.106 --> 46:46.412
Really.

46:46.455 --> 46:48.022
- Yeah.

46:48.066 --> 46:50.285
I'll let you say good-bye.

46:55.943 --> 46:58.032
- Hey, Pac.

46:58.076 --> 47:01.993
I'll miss you.
- Me too.

47:02.036 --> 47:04.212
- Hey, you know, it's okay

47:04.256 --> 47:07.520
if things are hard sometimes.

47:07.563 --> 47:10.001
You can still be a good person,

47:10.044 --> 47:11.524
and have a really good life.

47:11.567 --> 47:14.048
That's what I want for you.

47:14.092 --> 47:17.008
This is good, a fresh start.

47:17.051 --> 47:19.010
[soft music]

47:19.053 --> 47:20.272
♪

47:20.315 --> 47:24.058
You can put the bad things
behind you.

47:24.102 --> 47:26.887
- Yeah.

47:26.931 --> 47:29.237
You too.

47:33.198 --> 47:35.417
- I'm trying, I am.

47:35.461 --> 47:37.115
But I'll admit,

47:37.158 --> 47:41.771
it's getting harder to live
with so much heartbreak.

47:41.815 --> 47:46.907
And there are days,
I just don't believe in love.

47:46.951 --> 47:50.084
I tell myself
to keep my heart open,

47:50.128 --> 47:53.000
that in the end,
I was wrong about you.

47:53.044 --> 47:56.134
Every relationship teaches us
hard lessons, right?

47:56.177 --> 47:58.310
That's their gift,
to make us ready for the day

47:58.353 --> 48:02.575
when someone,
maybe the one, walks in

48:02.618 --> 48:05.056
who could truly love us...

48:05.099 --> 48:06.579
[clanging]

48:06.622 --> 48:09.321
And we could truly love them.

48:09.364 --> 48:11.801
♪

48:11.845 --> 48:13.978
Well.

48:14.021 --> 48:16.937
Hello, there.

48:16.981 --> 48:18.983
Who are you?

48:19.026 --> 48:21.333
You've got that hoodie.

48:21.376 --> 48:23.639
You don't like
to be stared at.

48:23.683 --> 48:26.338
But your legs are bare.

48:26.381 --> 48:30.342
You like a little attention.

48:30.385 --> 48:33.040
Okay, I'll bite.

48:33.084 --> 48:36.043
[tense music]

48:36.087 --> 48:43.137
♪

48:46.053 --> 48:48.316
- Hey, bunny.

48:48.360 --> 48:50.057
- Candace.

48:50.101 --> 48:53.713
You're--
- Alive.

48:53.756 --> 48:55.845
Yeah, so uh...

48:55.889 --> 48:59.545
I think we have some unfinished
business to talk about.
